Taylor coefficients expansion of $E(z)$ as as a function
of $w_0$ and an arbitrary power $k$ of $1 + z$.

$$
F(x; w_0; k) = 2\sum_{{n=0}}^{{\infty}} \binom{{-\frac{{1}}{{2}}}}{{n}}
\frac{{x^n}}{{\left(1 - 2k - 6nw_0\right)}}
$$

We include terms up to $n=16$.

# Parameters

\{w0}
\{zpower}

# Returns

array_like

: The Taylor expansion coefficients.

Compute the $E(z)$ function for a flat wCDM cosmology.

$$
E(z; \Omega_{{m,0}}, w_0) = \sqrt{{\Omega_{{m,0}} (1 + z)^3
+ (1 - \Omega_{{m,0}}) (1 + z)^{{3(1 + w_0)}}}}
$$

